25|$|The {{layout of}} both Scout and Triplane was {{determined}} {{largely by the}} Admiralty requirement to carry a quick-firing, recoilless Davis gun that used 2lb (1kg) shells. At the time, {{there was no way}} of synchronising such a weapon with the propeller, or of mounting it elsewhere than the fuselage, so a pusher configuration was necessary, the pilot sitting in a nacelle with <b>the</b> <b>gun</b> <b>in</b> its nose.|$|E
